needsSave

boolean needsSave()
Returns true if the information about the model needs to be saved; false otherwise. This method should also consider changes to the associated metadata (see metadataChanged()). E.g., if the user moves a node of a FSAGraph, this method will return true since the updated position of the node has to be saved.

Returns:
true if the information maintained by the model needs to be saved; false otherwise

getParentModel

ParentModel getParentModel()
Returns the parent model, if any, of the model.

The parent model of a model is the model which is responsible for the maintenance of the child model, e.g., keeping track of changes, saving and loading, etc. If a model has a parent model, IDES will treat the child model as a temporary "view" into the parent model (e.g., it will not ask to save the model on closing, it will not allow renaming of the model, etc.)

Returns:
the parent model of the model; null if there is no parent

model - the parent model for the model

getEventSet

DESEventSet getEventSet()

the set of events in the model.
